  "prompt": "What are the various Incarnations of Lord Vishnu and what is going to be the last Incarnation of Lord Vishnu?",
  "response": "According to Hindu mythology, Lord Vishnu has ten primary incarnations (Dashavatara) that appear during different yugas (ages) to restore dharma and protect the world from evil. Here are the ten incarnations in their traditional order:\n\n1. Matsya (Fish) - Appeared during the Satya Yuga\n2. Kurma (Tortoise) - Appeared during the Satya Yuga\n3. Varaha (Boar) - Appeared during the Satya Yuga\n4. Narasimha (Half-man, Half-lion) - Appeared during the Satya Yuga\n5. Vamana (Dwarf Brahmin) - Appeared during the Treta Yuga\n6. Parashurama (Warrior Brahmin) - Appeared during the Treta Yuga\n7. Rama (Prince of Ayodhya) - Appeared during the Treta Yuga\n8. Krishna (Prince of Dwarka) - Appeared during the Dvapara Yuga\n9. Buddha (Enlightened One) - Appeared during the Kali Yuga\n10. Kalki (Warrior on a White Horse) - Yet to appear, will come at the end of Kali Yuga\n\nThe last and final incarnation of Lord Vishnu is prophesied to be Kalki, who will appear at the end of the Kali Yuga to destroy evil and restore righteousness. According to Hindu scriptures, Kalki will arrive on a white horse, wielding a sword, and will establish a new era of dharma.",
